 I agree copying is a much more nuanced issue- but sometimes struct is<br>&gt; close<br>&gt; &gt; enough.<br>&gt; &gt;<br>&gt; &gt; What I would really like is &quot;this is a data-only type&quot; rather than<br>&gt; &gt; &quot;struct&quot;.<br>&gt;<br>&gt; I&#39;m not sure what you mean by “data-only,” but the constraint I want is<br>&gt; “has value semantics.”<br>&gt;<br>&gt; --<br>&gt; -Dave<br>&gt;<br>&gt; _______________________________________________<br>&gt; swift-evolution mailing list<br>&gt; swift-evolution at swift.org<br>&gt; https://lists.swift.org/mailman/listinfo/swift-evolution<br>&gt;<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20161021/702fb604/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
